<item>
            <title>[OAK-3354] Clock.Fast delays repository shutdown</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/OAK-3354</link>
                <project id="12313221" key="OAK">Jackrabbit Oak</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Clock.Fast instance in RepositoryImpl schedules a tasks, which updates&lt;br/&gt;
the time field every 10 ms. This task is not canceled on RepositoryImpl.shutdown()&lt;br/&gt;
and therefore delays the shutdown because the executor must be terminated&lt;br/&gt;
forcefully in RepositoryImpl.closeExecutor(). &lt;/p&gt;</description>
